      "writtenOn": "2017-12-05T17:41:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027d go for retrying indefinitely because one should never have to restart monasca-api manually once influxdb is operational once more (there may after all be a whole cluster of monasca-api instances to deal with, along with poor configuration management that requires waiting a long time to run or that even requires you to restart things manually...). As for sleep time...hmm, good question. I\u0027d go for something on the order of 10 to 30 seconds. That will create a fair amount of visible spam in the log file. This will stand out to whoever debugs the problem but it won\u0027t be so much spam that it ends up overflowing the disk any time soon.\n\nAlso, definitely nothing dynamic/fancy such as exponential backoff: while that may be gentle in terms of load caused by failed attempts, it will also render monasca-api inoperable for a good while longer than influxdb\u0027s actual down time after a couple of failed attempts.",
      "parentUuid": "df87a7cf_c143ccae",
